<subSubSection id="8AF477F4FFACFF971CEBFF53FC1C6FB0" pageId="13" pageNumber="162" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C251247FFFACFF971CEBFF53FC1C6FB0" blockId="13.[151,1437,151,249]" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">
<emphasis id="F09AF86DFFACFF971CEBFF53FED16FF8" bold="true" box="[151,267,151,177]" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="05EE5FFCFFACFF971D69FF53FE1A6FF9" authorityName="Collin" authorityYear="1933" box="[277,448,151,176]" class="Insecta" family="Brachystomatidae" genus="Hyperperacera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F09AF86DFFACFF971D69FF53FE1A6FF9" box="[277,448,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">Hyperperacera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on one species from southern 
<collectingCountry id="BAF964EFFFACFF97185DFF53FBBA6FF8" box="[1057,1120,151,177]" name="Chile" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">Chile</collectingCountry>
, characterized by vein R 
<subScript id="5E6A263AFFACFF9719FFFF6DFA476FFE" attach="left" box="[1411,1437,169,183]" fontSize="6" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">4+5</subScript>
simple and arista placed slightly before the end of the very small postpedicel. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="A67F598EFFACFF9718D2FF7FFF016FB0" author="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M." pageId="13" pageNumber="162" pagination="27 - 37" refId="ref12184" refString="Sinclair, B. J. &amp; Cumming, J. M. (2007) Leptopezella, a new Southern Hemisphere genus of Ocydromiinae (Diptera: Empidoidea: Hybotidae). Zootaxa, 1629 (1), 27 - 37. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1629.1.2" type="journal article" year="2007">Sinclair &amp; Cumming (2007</bibRefCitation>
, p. 37), it is mostly likely congeneric with 
<taxonomicName id="05EE5FFCFFACFF971EC7FF1BFC1C6FB0" authority="Philippi." authorityName="Philippi." box="[699,966,223,249]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Heterophlebus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="162" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F09AF86DFFACFF971EC7FF1BFC856FB0" box="[699,863,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="162">Heterophlebus</emphasis>
Philippi.
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
